  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "How people think, perceive, and act can not be separated from their embedding in a socio-material world (Gahrn-Andersen 2019b).",
    "Human presencing emphasizes how humans, as social beings, become entangled with complex past encounters with others and how their ongoing engagement with others ultimately shapes their being.",
    "The phenomenon of human presencing is, therefore, theoretically and methodologically deeply embedded in distributed (e.g., Hollan et al. 2000) and embodied (Chemero 2009) approaches to cognition.",
    "These approaches stress people's active role in bringing about aspects of their lived experience as they coordinate in and with their immediate environment.",
    "The paper introduces the phenomenon of human presencing as an aspect of human embodiment and explains how the re-evoking of past encounters with others has significant implications for human perception, action, and thought."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The phenomenon of human presencing is, therefore, theoretically and methodologically deeply embedded in distributed (e.g., Hollan et al. 2000) and embodied (Chemero 2009) approaches to cognition."
  ]
